princess of bahrain dies five years after marriage
princess meles harriet harriet of bahrain married american marines johnson , who had won widespread praise from us television stations . however , this troubled marriage lasted for five years , but it has now come to a close in las vegas .
meili , a member of the royal family of bahrain in the gulf country , once became the main theme of a tv film , where johnson took the risk of losing his military life to participate in this forbidden love song .
however , according to a commentary in las vegas , it took five years for the two to appeal to the court for a divorce , where they were getting married quickly .
they met in 1999 when johnson was still a professional soldier stationed in bahrain .
after learning about this vivacious little princess , the sparks of love between the two have given rise to tremendous changes in his life .
the royal family banned the combination of these little lovers and gave birth to mei li'an , allowed her to wear velvet shirts , wear a baseball cap , and secretly bring her out of the motherland and to the united states according to military documents .
after a tough immigration lawsuit with the us authorities , the young couple finally married in the candle light church on the magnificent las vegas avenue when johnson , 23 , the new girl was only 19 .
johnson , however , said that because las vegas , known as the " sin city " , had lured him and merlian 's parents , who had strong financial strength , had always been tense and had been spreading rumors about a plot to assassinate him . this troubled marriage finally could not survive .
johnson said that he relied on guests of hotels and casinos to park their life while melancholia gradually caught in the night of the gambling town and frequently went up to the night shop to keep her husband out of sight .
mei li'an left the office one year ago .
johnson said , " she is alive . "
euro zone economic indicators to show continued weak economy in europe
economists said that the euro zone economic indicators to be released this week will show further evidence of weak economic confidence and slowing down in economic output , while britain 's data is expected to show an increase in industrial activity .
they said the economic output data of the biggest country in the euro zone would continue to show great fluctuations every month , but the long - term trend of economic output would show a slowdown .
the most important economic indicators for this week will provide evidence of european economic confidence in the first economic indicators to be released on the 7 th in germany and the market .
the pmug index dropped sharply from 31.3 in the previous month to 13.9 in november .
economists said that the substantial appreciation of the euro would continue to affect economic confidence in recent surveys , so there is no reason to predict a rebound in economic expectations .
economists of the nba said : " considering the main factors leading to the decline in economic confidence , including the appreciation of the euro , uncertain factors in the global economy , and unemployment rate which has worsened the german job market , all have a bearing on the anticipated future growth in december . therefore , it is not possible for the index to rebound strongly . "
according to a survey conducted by afp 's financial news dax to economists , this index will fall again from 11.9 percent in the previous month to 11 percent in december .
however , the target for the development of the industry is likely to fall to zero by december , the governor of the pbma said .
" the future of economic activities in germany , according to our view , will continue to decrease as reflected by the investigation of analysts and participants in the financial market , " tize said .
tension in ukraine due to crisis
russia has accused the west of interfering in east european affairs on numerous occasions because ukraine 's political crisis is getting the focus of attention and the annual meeting of the organization for security and cooperation in europe ( osce ) is set to be the main agenda .
western forces are gradually extending their sphere of influence to europe , which has been viewed by russia as their backyard . for example , the baltic countries , georgia and central asia have long been quite dissatisfied with russia . therefore , when osce is holding its two - day meeting in sofia , the capital city of bulgaria , its recent events may become an important topic of discussion .
the supreme court of ukraine made a dramatic ruling asking for a second round of voting in the recent presidential election . before that , the european union had called on members of the organization for security and cooperation in europe ( osce ) to prepare for " the fastest and efficient action " for observers .
the number of observers sent by the osce may increase from 600 to 1,000 in ukraine 's december 26 recount , european sources said .
us secretary of state colin powell will attend the osce annual meeting , which may be his last foreign visit before leaving office .
russian foreign minister lavrov , french foreign minister barnier , british foreign minister straw , and german foreign minister fischer will also attend .
osce members include 55 countries in north america , europe and asia , and will celebrate the 30th anniversary of its founding next year .
the organization was founded in helsinki that year and has contributed to the end of the cold war .
bush 's intelligence reform bill faces congress vote this week
the intelligence reform bill , to be passed this week by the us congress with all efforts , is an ambitious administrative plan pushed by republican president bush for the second term , and his support among republican lawmakers is facing a major test for the first time since he was reelected .
keane , former republican governor of new jersey , who was responsible for investigating the terrorist attacks on new york and washington on september 11 , 2001 , said in a newspaper interview yesterday that the issue of the intelligence reform act was passed by congress , and that alone this incident had bad intentions on future cooperation between the two parties and on domestic policies of the president .
keane said : " if the president and congress fail to properly handle these major issues , the congress will become less functional and we will have trouble . "
he told the daily news in new york : " we have been waiting for a long time to have another bill that will win the support of republican and democratic leaders in both the senate and the house of representatives , as well as 80 percent of public support . "
several congressmen said yesterday that if the historic reform bill fails , it will delay thorough overhaul of the us old spy network system for several months , even several years , or even completely harm its existence .
al - haman , democratic member of the house intelligence committee , said on cnn yesterday , " it will die in placenta if the bill fails to be passed this week . "
congress will try to pass the " 2005 intelligence reform and terrorism prevention and control act " again on the 6th and 7th of next year , and then adjourned until early next year .
if the bill fails to be passed , it will become invalid and will not be redrafted until 2005 .
ukrainian opposition rejects revision of constitution
ukraine 's pro - western opposition parties insisted today that they would not accept a constitutional reform initiated by outgoing president kuchema before a second round of presidential elections .
the constitutional reform will deprive the majority of the current president 's power .
after the second round of voting in the supreme court , which declared november 21 as invalid , the central election commission urged the opposition leader viktor yushchenko to once again be deadlocked with kuchekov on december 26 .
" if the constitutional amendment is passed in the current form , all the powers of the president will be transferred to the parliament , which is unacceptable , " said viktor stefanko , president of the federation of soviet union .
" we hope the president will appoint the director of intelligence and the chief prosecutor so that we can fight corruption and get rid of the group that controls ukraine 's political and business sectors , " she told reporters .
kuchekov , who maintained close ties with russia , pushed for the revision of the constitution before holding a presidential election because he was worried that the opposition could win .
opposition congressmen yesterday refused to vote on the constitutional amendment proposed by the government , and the congress was adjourned for 10 days .
according to the constitutional amendment , apart from the prime minister , the defense minister , and the foreign minister , the power of appointment of all the heads of government will be transferred from the president to the congress . at present , forces supporting the government have nearly a majority in congress .
according to the contents of the amendment , the candidates for the prime minister , the defense minister , and the foreign minister appointed by the president will have to be approved by the congress , and the congress may also propose their candidates .
ukraine 's political crisis enters third week
ukrainian opposition leader viktor yushchenko today called for support for continuing street protests in ukraine 's presidential election by surrounding the presidential palace and the government building until outgoing president kuchekov and his cabinet prime minister yuri yaakunkovic and their cabinet members take actions to ensure fairness of the forthcoming presidential election .
tens of thousands of ukrainian supporters gathered in the capital kiev for two weeks to encircle the government building and sleep in the street of the soviet experts as the main avenue for the military parade . the people they displayed forced the supreme court to declare november 21 a second round of presidential election invalid . the central election commission issued an order on december 26 to hold a re - election . the parliament has not yet signed an executive order to replace the successor .
viktor yushchenko told the crowd of support people gathered in the capital 's independent square tonight that kuchema should replace his government , reorganize his central election commission , and both parliament and kuchema should agree to amend the election law to prevent any corrupt election practices .
" before making these decisions , we cannot talk about removing the siege to the government building or the presidential palace , " he said in a speech opening the prelude to the december 26 election .
in the past 14 days , this square has demonstrated great love for ukraine and the civic awareness of millions of ukrainian people who can defend their choice . "
he said : " we are going through a struggle between good and evil forces . the whole world is applauding our victory . the whole world is proud of ukraine . "
at a time when the opposition party is intensifying its pressure on the ruling authorities in moscow , viktor yushchenko and kuchekov are once again deadlocked in their constitutional reform . polish president kwasniewski , lithuanian president marcoux , and russian special envoy gerzlov are scheduled to arrive in kiev on the 6th for another round of mediation .
egypt sees breakthrough in mideast peace process
egypt said that the middle east peace accord is expected to have a new framework .
it also said that it might send new ambassadors back to israel in the near future to restore the comprehensive diplomatic relations that had been suspended for four years .
egypt 's state - run middle east news agency quoted " senior egyptian officials " as saying that the parties seeking a peace plan have gradually reached a consensus on comprehensive reconciliation .
the middle east news agency said : " egypt , israel , palestine and major international organizations , such as the united states and the european union , have reached an important understanding and agreed in principle to completely resolve the conflicts between israel and palestine . "
since palestinian strong arafat passed away last month , the international community has been pushing for the restoration of the middle east peace policy with a view to ending the bloody conflict between israel and palestine for many years at an early date .
the middle east news agency said that officials predict that " preparations will be carried out in july and then political actions will be taken again . "
the middle east news agency said that following that , israel and palestine , as well as egypt , the united states , russia and several european countries will hold meetings in washington .
it is expected that the meeting will cover " a cease - fire between the two sides " . palestinian authority will " stop anti-israel attacks " and strengthen its control over the gaza strip and the west bank . "
regarding this , the middle east news agency said israeli prime minister sharon promised " israel will stop its military actions against the palestinians so long as the palestinian authorities respect the cease - fire agreement and control their areas well . "
more than 1 billion children suffer from war aids
an annual report released by the united nations children 's fund ( unicef ) today pointed out that more than one - billion children , or more than half of the world 's children , suffered from poverty , wars , and aids .
unicef said in a statement that children 's rights , which was clearly defined by the 1989 convention on children 's rights , were often harmed , partly due to the failure of governments to implement human rights and economic reforms .
" when half of the children in the world grow hungry and unhealthy , when schools become targets of attack and the entire village are destroyed with aids , we are unable to honor our promise to the children , " said ms. bellamy , executive chairman of the unicef 's executive committee in london in an annual report .
berri added : " the governments of too many countries are making a realistic , intentional choice that harms children . "
the united nations children 's fund ( unicef ) , the london institute of economics and the university of brisbane in the united kingdom ( uk ) and researchers in the united kingdom jointly compiled statistics to expose children 's terror in most parts of the world .
researchers found that about 64 million children in the world are lacking proper accommodation , 400 million children are unable to get safe drinking water , 270 million children are unable to enjoy health services , and 140 million ( mostly girls ) have never studied .
researchers pointed out that , more importantly , at least 700 - million children suffered from various forms of " serious exploitation , " including inability to access information and enjoy public health facilities .
the united nations children 's fund ( unicef ) said in its 10 th annual report that wars and aids had destroyed all kinds of networks that were usually able to protect children , and children became victims of wars and aids from time to time .
china puts pressure on eu to lift arms embargo
the european union today rejected chinese premier wen jiabao 's call for ending pressure on china 's arms embargo as soon as possible , but also said that it would make efforts to move toward lifting the 15 - year embargo .
the netherlands , the rotating president of the european union ( eu ) , made the above statement after the china - eu summit .
the netherlands said that it is not necessary to make wild speculation about how the eu should stop this embargo from drawing .
the european union imposed arms embargo on beijing after the 1989 tiananmen massacre .
although the issue of arms embargo cast a shadow on this china - eu summit , the two sides still signed several trade and other agreements at the meeting .
china and the eu both claim that these agreements have strengthened their " strategic partnership " .
in a joint statement issued after the summit meeting between the eu and chinese premier wen jiabao , the eu said , " the eu has confirmed its political intention to continue its efforts to lift the embargo . "
the statement pointed out that the chinese delegation " welcomes this positive news and believes that this message is conducive to the healthy development of the broad strategic partnership between china and the eu . "
at a press conference after the summit , wen jiabao did not conceal his unhappiness . he said the embargo " did not reflect the partnership between china and the eu . "
wen jiabao said , " the embargo is the result of the cold war . it cannot reflect the current situation , still less reflects the partnership between china and the european union . "
some eu countries , led by france , pushed for the lifting of the arms embargo , claiming that it is outdated .
without revising the relevant eu laws , people of foresight in the eu are worried that lifting the embargo may open up the protective gate for arms sales , which will boost china 's military strength .
dutch prime minister baskean said , " i explained that the eu is willing to lift the embargo . however , i also pointed out that there is a relationship between lifting the ban and adjusting the code of conduct for arms exports . "
initial findings show that folic acid may lead to breast cancer but no final conclusion
according to the latest health research report , pregnant women will increase the chance of getting breast cancer by taking a type of vitamin b acid that is commonly used in order to prevent fetus 's abnormal change .
however , researchers said their research results might be accidental because other studies show that folic acid actually reduces the risk of getting breast cancer . therefore , they urge pregnant women to continue to take this supplement .
acidity in ye will naturally exist in dark - coloured folic vegetables , and the medical community knows that this is an important boost to the development of embryos .
researchers from the two universities of brisbane and arbner in the united kingdom followed up 3,000 women who took 5 mg or 0.2 mg of folic acid or placebo when they were pregnant in the 1960 s , most of which were in their second and third pregnancy .
the report published in the british medical journal pointed out that as of september 2002 , women who had consumed five mg of folic acid had breast cancer , which was only twice as high as that of placebo .
researcher nye stressed that this result was only " preliminary . " its purpose is to point out a way of further study . "
he said : " it is entirely possible that this is the result of an accident . therefore , before we reach any conclusion , we have to conduct further scientific research to review the interrelationship . if the link exists , "
nicosia said that women planning to be pregnant should still take ingredients of folic acid .
he said that currently there is a considerable gap between the dosage and the experimental dosage .
according to the uk 's hygiene standards , women who wish to be pregnant and in their pregnancy in phase 1 should take 0.4 mg of folic acid per day , 10 times smaller than the dosage taken by women in the above study .
