romania 's opposition candidate , adrian jeremy , won the fierce presidential election here today , but the mayor of bucharest , the centre - right city in the middle , is likely to face tremendous challenges because there are many parliamentary parties in the country .
according to the final official results released by the romanian central election commission today , the " justice and truth union " candidate barghuti won 51.23 percent of the vote . his opponent and prime minister nastase got 487.7 percent of the votes .
nastase admitted his defeat and congratulated palestine 's shehr .
president iloilo , who is about to step down , has also congratulated pakistan on his departure from office .
