bush admits that training of iraqi troops needs to be enhanced , rumsfeld
us president bush admitted today that iraqi troops had not been well prepared to replace us forces and warned that the general election scheduled to be held on january 30 next year would not be the end of a serious riot in iraq .
at a one - hour press conference , bush also expressed his support for secretary of defense rumsfeld , firmly believing that the pentagon chief would " do whatever he takes . "
bush said he vowed to continue cooperation with russian president vladimir putin despite the sometimes serious discord and that it was time to move on the path of ending the middle east conflict .
he also believes that the best way to deal with the issue of iraq and north korea , a surviving " axis of evil , " is to deal with it through diplomacy between countries .
yesterday , a series of car bomb attacks took place in two iraqi shiite holy city najaf and karbala . after 66 people were killed and more than 200 injured , bush admitted that the riot had caused the iraqi people to pay a price . however , he insisted that the january general election would proceed as usual .
bush issued a warning to the american people that the election in iraq was " just the beginning of the political process " and warned that " i certainly would not think the process would be smooth sailing . "
bush also admitted that the training results of the iraqi security forces were good or bad .
he said , " they ( iraqi troops ) will escape from the battlefield in some instances of fierce fighting . "
he said that this kind of iraqi force will never be able to protect national security , which is unacceptable .
but he believes that after a long period of training by the us military , the training of iraqi troops will achieve results .
white house : iraqi rebels attempt to disrupt election doomed to failure
in response to an attack by rebels at a us military base restaurant in mosul in northern iraq at noon today , 22 us and iraqi soldiers were killed and more than 60 people were injured . white house spokesman mcclellan said that with the advances of the election in iraq , terrorist activities by iraqi rebels will be more rampant , but these " enemies of freedom " will surely be eliminated .
