russian president vladimir putin said monday that russia 's acquisition of russian oil giant yukos 's main assets was to protect national interests and was also the first attempt to regain nationalization of the former soviet union .
" russia is now using an absolutely legal market mechanism to protect its national interests , " putin said at a year - end press conference in the kremlin , referring to the acquisition of yukos oil and gas company , a subsidiary of russian state - owned oil companies .
i think this practice is completely normal . "
russian state - run oil companies became their new boss today after purchasing baikal financial group of the russian - based basque petroleum and natural gas company , which previously held secret auctions .
russian state - owned oil companies announced late wednesday that they had already obtained 100 percent of shares of previously unknown baikal financial group .
the acquisition will enable the kremlin to firmly control russia 's key energy industry .
russian authorities have been attacking yukos and its prison founder in the past 18 months .
the state - owned oil company and the russian state gas company are merging , and the three oil and gas companies , together , will be in charge of one - fifth of russia 's total oil output and the production of all natural gas , making them the world 's largest energy group .
putin defended the country 's acquisition today by attacking the privatized boxes in the 1990s .
privatization measures at that time brought the most valuable assets of the russian economy into the hands of a small number of eight - faced excellent businessmen , such as khodorkovski .
baikal financial group previously offered a bid of 9350 million us dollars to purchase the controlling power of the yukos oil and natural gas corporation .
