japanese ministry of civil affairs to try out electronic communication service to reduce pressure on office life
the japanese ministry of civil affairs began an advanced internet program today , hoping that by 2010 , 20 percent of the japanese workforce will be able to carry out " electronic mail delivery " work from home to reduce the pressure brought about by office life and the breakup of families .
about four million japanese , or six percent of japan 's 63.2 million workforce , were working outside the office using technology , a chief cabinet ministry official said .
beginning january , the ministry of civil affairs will have six staff members working at home , universities or libraries without going into the office for at least one day .
the ministry of home affairs will then expand the scope of this kind of advanced program , up to 20 percent of the entire 2,500 staff of the ministry of education will be able to work at home by 2006 .
this allows staff to attend meetings on the internet chat room and in the hope of " increasing the efficiency " , the chief of the ministry of home affairs said .
he said that the e - channels would allow the labour sector more time to get along with their families and help those who were in financial need to live home .
he said the scheme would also reduce traffic congestion , including the free flow of vehicles and congestion at peak times .
he said : the goal of this program is to " increase the percentage of japanese electronics users to 10 percent by 2005 through encouraging sharing of electronic payment services with private enterprises . by 2010 , it will further increase to 20 percent . "
pentagon launches unprecedented relief operation for tsunami victims in asia
the pentagon said today that it had launched its largest rescue operation in history to help tsunami victims in asia , including two aircraft carrier battle groups , 20 aircraft including reconnaissance and supply planes , and tens of thousands of people .
heks , a spokesman for the pentagon and a naval school , said that the us military was facing the challenge of simultaneously conducting operations in several areas after the tsunami disaster that killed more than 80,000 people on the 26th .
he told afp : " this is one of the largest humanitarian relief operations in the pentagon 's history . "
lieutenant general conway , an officer in charge of military operations at the joint chiefs of staff , said that they are seeking an assessment of the scale of the disaster and have sent a disaster relief assessment team to thailand , sri lanka and indonesia .
the pentagon said that 20 planes have been dispatched to south asia , including six cbc - 130 transport planes transporting drinking water and food , five kaz - 135 air refueling planes , and nine p3 reconnaisance planes .
the pentagon also mobilized the aircraft carriers , the aircraft carrier " lin " and " li cha , " and their ships .
corwell said , " the linka battle group and its 12 helicopters and 9,000 personnel have arrived at siem reap bay from hong kong and will eventually be deployed in the sea off soares . "
the " li cha " , carrying 25 helicopters , 2,100 marines and 1,400 marines , has left guam and is expected to arrive in bengal before 7 january .
the pentagon has decided to mobilize five more ships from guam and two ships capable of producing fresh water from diego garcia in the indian ocean .
the us forces will be directing the operation at the uta base in thailand at siem reap bay , hong said .
