japan today promised to provide 500 - million us dollars in aid to countries affected by the indian ocean 's massive tsunami as countries vied to provide relief for the world 's worst disaster victims , the aid jumped to first place in all countries and increased the total amount of relief and reconstruction funds promised to date to 1.6 - billion us dollars .
japanese prime minister junichiro koizumi said in a statement that japan , as the biggest economy in asia , will consider providing more aid , including money and technology .
he said : " japan will do its best to provide assistance in three areas : financial resources , knowledge technology and human resources . "
he said , " japan will temporarily grant 500 - million us dollars as emergency aid to disaster - stricken countries and relevant international organizations . "
koizumi also said he would attend a meeting of world leaders on the 6 th in the indonesian capital of jakarta to discuss aid to countries affected by the tsunamis .
after us president bush was criticized for being slow in responding to the catastrophe of mankind , the us government yesterday increased its promised aid by 10 times to 350 million us dollars .
china , which has been viewed as a growing challenge to japan 's influence in asia , has also promised to provide us $ 60.5 million in aid , which is a big figure for developing countries .
" japan will mobilize helicopters and personnel to make more contributions , " koizumi said .
japan will also consider deploying more forces as soon as possible , including aircraft , warships , and personnel of the japanese self-defense force . "
japan had previously promised to provide 30 million us dollars in aid to countries victimized by the tsunami .
a foreign ministry spokesman said that the $ 500 million koizumi mentioned also includes this $ 30 million dollar .
who : 50 groups to provide indonesia with medical aid
fifty aid groups have arrived in indonesia 's aceh province to provide medical assistance to survivors , the world health organization said tuesday .
the world health organization ( who ) is trying to coordinate all its groups and has held a meeting with them this afternoon , who 's representative peter pag said .
peter said it was very difficult to coordinate because many groups had already gone directly to aceh to carry out relief work .
peter said in a telephone interview in jakarta : " we are trying to find out the truth . every group has just arrived , but each group has expressed that they are willing to cooperate . "
peter said the main concern of the who is to prevent the outbreak of epidemics , such as cholera and bacillus , which could cause tens of thousands of deaths .
" we are very worried because many of us are homeless . they do n't have enough clean water or proper food , " peter said .
therefore , conditions are already ripe for the outbreak of infectious diseases . "
however , he stressed that there is no sign of the disease so far .
the indonesian ministry of health said that the death toll of sumatra could be as high as 100,000 , mostly in aceh province .
as most of the medical facilities in aceh have been destroyed , in the past week the indonesian military , the government of singapore and australia have set up at least eight field hospitals , and the united nations children 's fund has also started to send basic medical packets to help 200,000 children .
