foreign relief forces are airdropping food and building a clean water supply system in the tsunami - stricken areas in asia to help millions of homeless and famine victims .
according to statistics , the death toll has risen to nearly 150,000 .
the governments of various countries have been continuously providing relief supplies . us president bush entrusted his father , senior bush , and former president clinton to be responsible for soliciting donations from the people .
as for the us delegation headed by secretary of state colin powell , they arrived in thailand last night before a crisis summit meeting in jakarta , the capital of indonesia , to express us concern and assess the progress of rescue work .
powell 's entourage includes president bush 's younger brother , governor of florida jesse bush , and director of the us international development agency natos .
powell will lead a delegation to inspect the disaster situation in thailand , indonesia , and sri lanka and participate in the summit meeting on the 6th .
powell said that the purpose of his visit is to assess the disaster situation and observe what the united states needs to do . however , he promised to immediately increase aid without making a commitment of 350 - million us dollars .
since the disaster , there have been calls for giving up the search for thousands of unknown tourists , many of whom are foreign tourists .
however , thai prime minister thaksin vowed to continue the search in his country .
" foreign experts told reporters on puji island that they ( the missing person ) might be buried in the mud of mangrove . we will continue to do our utmost to search for them and will not stop their pace , " thaksin told reporters .
the largest - scale international rescue operation in history is continuing .
the naval helicopter dispatched by the us aircraft carrier " linqi " has already carried out a second day of airdropping relief supplies and carrying survivors in indonesia 's aceh province .
rear admiral crawford , commander of the navy , said that 50 - thousand pounds of food and water have arrived in the disaster area . the mission has been carried out " smoothly . "
political struggle behind behind aid for tsunami disaster
while the sources of materials for rescuing the victims of the asian tsunami were flocking into the disaster areas , a rather unusual activity was also being secretly carried out : governments are investing in that area on the one hand , and on the other hand , they should get assistance , and on the other hand , they should lead this modern largest relief operation .
the catastrophe that caused nearly 150,000 deaths caused the old flames of war , including the discord between the united states , the united nations and europe , and the struggle for the leading position in asia .
however , disaster relief experts still have cautiously hoped that this tsunami attack on too many countries might lead to a precedent : the countries that promised to provide assistance would truly fulfill their promise .
" the aid commitments made by the governments of all countries have never been 100 percent timely , " said juma zhuoma , professor of international development at the harvard university school of government .
the governments of various countries have promised us $ 2 - billion in aid , including un secretary general annan , us secretary of state powell , and other world political leaders , including leaders of australia , china , and japan , will hold a crisis summit in jakarta on the 6th , which has a strong political significance .
after being accused of being slow in response and the open criticism of the " stingy " of rich countries , us president bush increased us aid to nearly 10 times , increasing by 350 - million us dollars .
in asia , the secret influence of the tsunami disaster on the region has increased confidence that china 's promise to provide 60.5 million us dollars in aid is a big hand for a developing country .
japan , which has reduced its foreign aid budget for six consecutive years , has also rapidly broken down its national strength with action and promised to raise at least $ 500 - million in aid . this is a bit too difficult for all other countries .
