xinhua news agency , abidjan , december 8 ( reporter liu shaoping ) - the un mission in cote d'ivoire issued a communique in abidjan on the evening of the 8th , saying that un secretary general annan welcomed the consensus reached by all parties concerned on continuing to implement the peace agreement and called on all parties concerned to seize this opportunity to ensure " real progress " in the peace process in preparation for the general election in october 2005 .
the communique says , at the same time , annan stressed that all sides in cote d'ivoire should reach a consensus on the " concrete action plan . "
he also " placed great hopes " on south african president mbeki and the african union for continuing to work together with the west african community and the united nations mission in cote d'ivoire to resolve the crisis in cote d'ivoire .
mbeki , entrusted by the african union , paid a four - day visit to cote d'ivoire from the 2 nd to the 6 th of this month in an effort to seek a solution to the crisis in cote d'ivoire .
at the end of the visit , mbeki announced that all sides in cote d'ivoire had reached consensus on the four - point proposal .
the proposed legislation includes the completion of the relevant legislation in the markuxi agreement , the beginning of an end to the armed conflict , the return of all ministers of the government to their posts to perform their duties , and the restoration of security in cote d'ivoire .
the parliament will discuss the draft revision of the constitution with effect from the 10 th .
the armed forces of cote d'ivoire also announced on the 8 th that leaders of the opposition armed forces will hold a meeting in the near future to make an overall assessment of the peace process and discuss the disarmament issue .
a coup and civil war broke out in september 2002 in cote d'ivoire .
in january last year and july this year , representatives of major opposition parties and armed forces of cote d'ivoire reached agreements with ghana , agreeing to resume peace and achieve national reconciliation .
however , the implementation of the agreement has suffered repeated setbacks , with the result that the peace process has suffered repeated setbacks .
in mid - october , the rebels in northern cote d'ivoire announced to recall their political representatives and that the peace process in cote d'ivoire has once again reached a deadlock .
in early november , the situation in cote d'ivoire worsened further after a serious clash between the government troops and french troops stationed in cote d'ivoire .
