xinhua news agency , washington , december 20th ( reporters pan yunzhao , tan xinmu ) - - u . s . defense secretary gordon england said at a press conference held at the pentagon on the 20th that a review team of the military has confirmed that a prisoner detained at the us naval base at guantanamo is not an enemy combat personnel , but will be released shortly .
this is the second guantanamo prisoner identified by the us military as not an enemy combat personnel .
england said that the pentagon confirmed the prisoner 's identity one or two days ago . the state department will inform the prisoner 's country of the decision and make arrangements for the release .
however , he did not disclose the name or nationality of the prisoner nor the circumstances under which he was arrested .
england refused to admit that the defense department had made mistakes in determining the identities of guantanamo prisoners .
he said that the military review team responsible for examining the identities of the guantanamo prisoners had examined 507 prisoners and confirmed the identities of 230 people , of which 228 were correct .
up to now , the united states has released about 200 guantanamo prisoners . some of them have been released after being repatriated , while a few others have been detained after returning home . however , at least 12 people have participated in the crackdown on the us military after being released .
at present , about 550 " al qaeda " and taliban suspects are being detained at the us naval base . most of them were captured during the us afghanistan war .
the us government claims that these people are enemy combat personnel , not prisoners of war , and therefore are not protected by the " geneva convention . "
