top state domain name nodes set up in shanghai
xinhua news agency , shanghai , december 21 ( feng yzhen , chen haiyu ) on the 21st , the china internet information center and the shanghai information industry ( group ) company , ltd. signed a contract to set up a state domain name top node in shanghai .
the domain name is a telecommunications basis for all internet applications , such as e - commerce and e - government . it is now widely used as an internet address .
when visiting websites and sending or sending e - mails , people have to first input domain names . through the dissecting and analysis services of the domain name system , they have to change their domain names to s . p addresses and find the main engine for web sites to realize information transmission .
the domain name system is like a " nerve system " that controls the transmission of internet information .
mao wei , director of the china internet information center , which manages china 's top domain name system , said that as of now , there are over 90 million internet users in china , ranking second in the world in terms of scale , and the number of websites has exceeded 650,000 .
with the rapid development of the internet , the number of applications for domain names has increased rapidly .
at present , the number of cnc domain names registered at a rate of 10,000 each month , reaching 433,000 .
the state 's top domain name server managed by the china internet information center handles more than 380 - million domain name analysis requests per day , with an average of over 4,400 per second , a peak of over 8,000 .
faced with the trend of rapid development of the internet , the china internet information center , the china domain name registration administration , will conduct a new appraisal this year of the top nodes of the country 's original four state domain name top nodes , and re - deploy its high - grade notional notional nodes according to the assessment conditions .
based on the local internet development level and the software and hardware conditions of the connecting unit , it has been decided to set up the top state domain name nodes in shanghai .
it has been learned that shanghai now has 45,000 ecn domain names , and its internet users have a rate of 26.6 percent , and its internet popularization rate and application level rank first in the country .
eastern china , which borders shanghai , has 130 , 000 sn domain names and 230,000 web sites , which also rank first in the development level .
for this reason , shanghai has been selected as the first node in the re - deployment plan .
china becomes world 's biggest producer of hard alloy
nanchang , december 22 , xinhua ( reporters yang ehiman and li xingwen ) china 's hard alloy industry has developed rapidly in recent years , with an annual output exceeding one third of the world 's output of hard alloy . as far as its production scale and output are concerned , china has become the number one producing country of the world 's hard alloy , with complete varieties of hard alloy , and most of its products in china can be produced .
this was learned by this reporter from the ongoing seminar on china 's ganzhou forestry development strategy on the 22 nd .
the hard alloy industry is called " industrial teeth " because of its high degree of strength and endurance for cutting off tools , high pressure tools , mining and road - building machinery . the development of the hard - quality alloy industry plays a very important role in the development of the entire industry .
china 's hard alloy started in the 1950 s and has grown from scratch and has made remarkable achievements since then .
in the early 1980 s , the annual output of china 's hard alloy was 25,000 tons , and the annual output of china 's hard alloy reached 38,000 tons in the 21 st century .
china has also made remarkable progress in exporting hard alloy .
china 's annual export of hard alloy in 1986 was only 100 tons , and by 2003 , its export volume is expected to exceed 3,000 tons , same as the output of the world 's hard alloy market , and its annual foreign exchange earning from the export of hard alloy has increased from less than 4 million us dollars in the past to 70 million us dollars per year .
adb approves electricity use in shanxi province
xinhua news agency , beijing , december 23 ( reporter jiang guocheng ) it was learned from the asian development bank 's representative office in china on the 23rd that the adb recently approved a loan of 174 million us dollars to support shanxi province 's southern construction of a power plant with octane octane gas to generate electricity .
the project will use the latest technology to increase the production of coalbed methane and coal fields to provide fuel for a 120,000 kilowatts of power plant in the near future .
according to the plan , the project will provide at least 166 million cubic meters of coalbed methane per year to about 90,000 families and industrial and commercial users in 2008 .
about 410,000 people in the jincheng area will benefit .
coal output in shanxi accounts for about one third of china 's total coal output .
the total cost of the project is estimated at 237 million us dollars , of which the japan bank for international cooperation will provide 20 million us dollars and the china construction bank will provide 37.86 million us dollars in loans .
the city government and the mining / industrial groups will provide a total of 612.24 million u.s. dollars in share capital .
the us trade and development agency has also provided a grant of 500,000 us dollars for the project .
the methane generated from the project is called coalbed methane from the mine through the surface to the underground coalbed , while the methane generated from the underground coal mining operation is called coal .
methane is a kind of highly explosive gas that needs to be discharged first in coal mining to ensure safety of the working environment .
removing , collecting and using methane will reduce greenhouse gas emissions and is conducive to slowing down global warming and climate change .
methane emissions 21 times carbon dioxide .
replacement of coal with methane can also increase the use of clean fuel , improve the efficiency of coal mines , and make the air cleaner .
the adb 's senior project expert , hansen , said that the project is expected to provide 4.5 million tons of carbon dioxide emission reduction .
