shenzhen to enforce ' water in some buildings ' and small areas
xinhua news agency , guangzhou , december 26 , as a major measure for building a " water - saving " city , shenzhen will forcefully promote the use of " water in water " in some relatively large buildings and small areas . at present , relevant water design standards and regulations are being formulated .
" water in water " mainly refers to non - potable water that can be reused to a certain extent after a certain amount of sewage or domestic sewage has been treated and treated .
the water quality is separated from polluted water discharged from the pipeline .
generally speaking , they use a great deal of water in flushing toilets , gardens , farmland irrigation , road preservation , car washing , urban jet spring , and fresh water replenishment equipment .
a survey conducted by the shenzhen municipal water administration shows that , in the mid - 1990s , more than 70 buildings in shenzhen city had a " chinese water " recycling facility . however , due to technical , design , and management factors , the cost of recycling " chinese water " was too high , and the construction unit had to give up its use .
to enable these pipes to truly play their role , they will only need to invest 300,000 to 400,000 yuan to install a " water treatment " system .
if more than 70 existing " chinese water " pipelines are used at present , calculating on the basis of 500 tons of " chinese water " per day in each small estate , shenzhen will be able to save 35,000 tons of tap water per day .
it is reported that the recall of water from shenzhen city will begin from the original 70 - odd buildings with a " chinese water " recovery system . after summing up experience , the work will be further popularized .
at the same time , the shenzhen water services department will work together with the urban planning and construction departments to formulate as soon as possible a set of standards for the design of " water in water " and stipulated that the use of " water in water " should be forcefully implemented in some relatively large buildings .
after the treatment , the " chinese water " will be used first in the greening irrigation of cities .
