china banking regulatory commission to strengthen supervision over financial asset management companies
xinhua news agency , beijing , december 29 ( reporter wang weiping ) - the china banking regulatory commission recently chaired a meeting on strengthening supervision and management over the disposal of bad assets . the meeting decided that supervisory departments would " treat both the symptoms and the cause " and earnestly strengthen supervision and management of financial asset management companies .
a relevant person in charge of the china banking regulatory commission said on the 29 th that the china banking regulatory commission will investigate and handle , according to law , violations of the law and regulations in the management and handling of bad assets , and transfer them to judicial organs for investigation and prosecution .
the results of handling major and typical cases should be disclosed to the public and subjected to social supervision by such means as making public the results of such cases .
in the near future , the csrc will focus on improving and strengthening its supervision and management mechanism over financial - assets management companies in four aspects : 1 .
first , it is necessary to speed up the building of relevant laws and regulations of the financial - assets management companies .
draw up a unified plan for the building of laws and regulations concerning the management of financial assets in order to solve the problem of imperfect laws and regulations governing financial - assets management companies .
the china banking regulatory commission will draft and publish as soon as possible the " guidelines on all the work of handling bad assets of financial - assets management companies , " the " measures for disclosing information of financial - assets management companies , " and the " measures for punishing illegal acts of financial - assets management companies . "
second , it is necessary to improve the mechanism for the management of financial - assets management companies and resolve , in terms of system , mechanism , and management , the issue of short - term behavior and moral risk in the operation of financial - assets management companies .
third , the supervision and management of financial - assets management companies should be strengthened and improved .
the supervisory and management departments of the financial - assets management companies should share the work and coordinate with one another , earnestly assume their supervisory and regulatory functions , form a joint force for supervision and management , and improve the efficiency of supervision .
fourth , it is necessary to continue to do a good job in policy investigation and study , promote the improvement of the external environment for the disposal of assets , including the market environment and legal and policy environment , and the construction of infrastructure facilities for transactions in bad assets .
( hong kong , macao and taiwan ) hong kong and macao residents to apply for setting up sole proprietors in shanghai to enjoy a " green passage "
xinhua news agency , shanghai , december 30 ( reporter yu lihong ) starting from january 1 , 2005 , hong kong and macao residents applying to set up individual business households in shanghai without obtaining approval from a foreign - funded department , their applications can be downloaded from the industrial and commercial website , and the city 's 20 industrial and commercial sub-bureaus will set up a " green passage " to process applications .
this reporter has learned from the shanghai municipal industrial and commercial administration bureau that the procedures for hong kong and macao residents to apply for setting up individual industrial and commercial households in shanghai are not complicated . the materials that need to be submitted include the " application for registration of individual industrial and commercial households ( hong kong and macao residents ) " signed by the applicant , the identity document and identity verification document of the applicant , the business establishment document , and other documents submitted by the state laws and regulations .
beginning 1 january 2005 , shanghai 's industrial and commercial administration department will set up special windows and " green passage " at 20 sub-bureaus in the municipality to provide one - stop services for hong kong and macao residents applying for registering , accepting , and approving their individual business households .
in addition , the shanghai industrial and commercial administration department has also launched a download version of the " registration forms for hong kong and macao residents bidding for individual industrial and commercial households in the mainland " on the official website ( www . smcs . gov . cn ) , which can be downloaded directly from the applicant 's website .
the applicants can also get relevant information through online consultations . the industrial and commercial website of shanghai will give answers within two working days to any issues that involve hong kong and macao residents applying for the registration of individual industrial and commercial households .
it is reported that the business scope of hong kong and macao residents applying for registration with individual industrial and commercial households in shanghai is as follows : retail ( excluding the retail sales of tobacco ) , restaurants , residents ' services , and other service trades , such as barber and beauty care services , bath services , repair of household electrical appliances , and other daily necessities , but they do not include licensed operation .
at the same time , the formation of individual industrial and commercial households in hong kong and macao is limited to individual business operations . they employ not more than eight people and have a business area not exceeding 300 square meters .
( international ) yugansk 's assets to be auctioned will not be included in russian natural gas industry shares
xinhua news agency , moscow , december 30 ( reporter song shiyi ) russian president 's office director and chairman of russian natural gas industry shareholding company medellin said to the media on the 30th that russian natural gas industry shareholding company will merge with russian oil companies as scheduled in january next year , but the assets of yugansk , the biggest subsidiary of russian oil company , will not be included in the assets of russian natural gas industry .
in addition , russian minister of industry and energy khristenko said on the same day that the assets of yugansk , which was auctioned off , would not be included in the assets of the russian natural gas industrial company , that this is mainly because the state is already the main shareholder of the russian oil and natural gas industry company , and the state does not want to increase its share in excess of the controlling share .
he said that yugansk 's assets will be stripped off alone and handed over to a completely owned company .
on the 19 th of this month , the russian federation property fund held an open auction of the 76.79% stake in yugansk , the largest yukos oil and natural gas company , at a price of 9.35 - billion us dollars .
on the 22 nd , the state - owned russian oil company announced that it had purchased baikal financial group , which won the bid for yugansk , to become a new holder of yugansk 's shares .
analysts believe that an important reason that russia is ingeniously operating in the auction of yugansk 's assets is because it is playing a leading role in related legal disputes .
in september this year , russian president putin approved the russian natural gas industry company to merge with the russian oil company .
the russian natural gas industry corporation was founded in february 1993 and is the largest natural gas exploitation company in the world .
the natural gas reserve of this company accounts for 65 percent of russia 's total .
last year , the corporation 's natural gas extraction volume accounted for 93 percent of russia 's total and 20 percent of the world 's total .
( tsunami ) tsunami hits indian state of tamil nadu
xinhua news agency , qinzhou , india , december 31 ( reporter jiang yaoping ) - the state of tamil nadu in the southeastern part of india is well - developed .
the state has a 1,000 - kilometer long coastline and exports 37,000 tons of seafood annually , earning 23.7 billion rupees ( one us dollar to 43 lubi ) to the local government .
however , a rare tsunami caused by the strong earthquake in the indian ocean on the 26 th caused unprecedented damage to local fisheries production .
according to an authoritative figure in the fishing industry in auye state , the unexpected disaster has had a tremendous impact on the state 's fisheries production .
because there was no prior warning or preparedness , the fishing boats were all parked in the harbor .
as a result , more than 7,000 aircraft and 30,000 barges , or more than 80 percent of all the boats in the state , were damaged in varying degrees .
the fishermen would not dare to go to the sea even if the fishing boats were repaired , because they saw for themselves the havoc and cruelty of the sea .
some people have bitterly lost their loved ones and damaged their property , and their psychological fear will stay for quite a long time .
it is estimated that the fishery output in the state in 2005 will be about 30 percent lower than in 2004 .
most of the coastal fishing villages in the state of tamil eelam have been hit by the tsunami disaster on the 26 th , becoming the worst hit in india .
as of 30 august , more than 6,230 people have died in the state , most of whom are fishermen .
some 6.8 million people in the state were affected by the tsunamis , 85 percent of whom were engaged in fishery production .
at present , the indian government is actively carrying out rescue work in an effort to restore local fishermen 's livelihood and fishery production as soon as possible .
shanghai airport bid farewell to old year and new year
xinhua news agency , shanghai , january 1 ( feng yizzhen , su haorong ) snow , freezing , and cold , staff members and workers of the shanghai airport bid farewell to the old days and greet the new in ice and snow .
after fighting against the ice and snow for two days , employees of the shanghai airport group welcomed their last flight in 2004 at 23:50 on the evening of the 31 st .
air china east china sea landed at shanghai 's pudong airport on the mc566 flights from sydney to shanghai , and the shipping production of the shanghai civil aviation came to a successful close in 2004 .
in 2004 , shanghai 's two major airports took off and landed nearly 330,000 sorties , up 35 percent from the previous year , transported 36 million passengers , 45 percent more than the previous year , and handled 2.25 million tons of cargo , up 40 percent from the previous year , with a net increase of 6.64 million tons .
in 2004 , the shanghai airport also added 16 new scheduled international air services cities , and the number of foreign airlines that newly opened shanghai 's scheduled flights reached five .
at present , 76 domestic cities and 86 international and regional cities have opened air routes with shanghai , 11 domestic airlines and 38 international and regional airlines operating scheduled flights to shanghai .
in the last two days of the new year , shanghai 's airport was once closed due to ice and snow , the parking area was full of airplanes , and a large number of flights were delayed .
however , thanks to the concerted efforts of civil aviation staff , the last day of the year ended , the air transportation was maintained smooth , and the operational order was restored to normal .
wu nianzu , president of the shanghai airport group , who was the first employee of the airport to guard against ice and snow , announced at midnight that the shanghai airport group had achieved its fifth safety year , and this was also the 17 th safety year for the hongqiao airport in shanghai .
wu nianzu said : in 2005 , the shanghai hongqiao airport will undergo a comprehensive renovation , the runway of the airport , the check - in process , the exterior of the waiting building , and so on ; the second runway of pudong airport will be put into use ; the waiting building of the first phase will be renovated ; and the passenger throughput of the two major airports in shanghai is expected to reach 42 - million in 2005 .
