xinhua news agency , fuzhou , january 5 ( wang fanfan , li bingyuan ) - according to information from relevant departments of shishi city , fujian province , in 2004 , the city 's per capita net income was 8038 yuan , an increase of 10 percent over the same period last year , ranking among all counties and cities in fujian province .
after the implementation of the tax reform in 2004 , the total annual burden on peasants in this city reached 7.2273 million yuan , with a reduction rate of 85.6% and a per capita burden of 41.5 yuan .
shishi , a famous chinese leisure garment city , won the titles of 100 strong counties ( cities ) and 10 strong counties ( cities ) in the national county economy that are basically competitive in the county economy .
since 2004 , this city has accelerated the process of building modern agriculture , and has achieved remarkable results in agriculture and rural work .
at present , shi'ao city in the whole province has taken the lead in connecting all villages with public transport , connecting all villages with water supply , and connecting all villages with cable television .
at present , the urbanization level of this city has reached 51 percent , ranking first among the county - level cities in the entire province .
this city has also vigorously integrated the minimum living standard of urban and rural residents with a new type of medical insurance for all the people in rural areas .
the standard of minimum guarantee for rural residents has been raised from 100 yuan per month to 200 yuan equal to that for urban residents .
a new type of rural medical insurance system for all people requires 60 yuan per person a year . peasants only need to pay 10 yuan per person . the rest will be borne by the financial authorities of cities and towns . at present , 106 - million peasants enjoy this policy .
in 2004 , shishi city 's budget for agricultural subsidies was 20.2 million yuan , an increase of 10.38% over the same period last year .
through the launching of free professional and technical training for rural labor force , a total of 1,017 laborers were transferred to other jobs in the whole year .
shi'ao city has also allocated 5 million yuan from its financial budget as funds for starting new projects and rewards for the transformation of old and new villages . at present , 86 new and heavy villages , or 85 percent of old administrative villages , have been built . the city plans to complete the task of transforming old villages in an all - round way by 2005 .
