( international ) chinese scientific expedition to climb highest on antarctic icecap
xinhua news agency , wassenaar , january 8 ( reporter cao yu and shen an ) zhang zhanhai , head of china 's 21st antarctic expedition team , said on the 8th that the chinese scientific expedition team has overcome many difficulties and reached about 50 kilometers from the highest point of the antarctic icecap - " dome - a " . it is expected that in the next two days , china will successfully climb to its top and become the world 's first country on board , which is called " extremely close to the earth . "
zhang zhanhai told xinhua reporters that one of the important objectives of this inspection tour is to prepare for the establishment of the third chinese scientific research station in the inland of the antarctic in the future and to build an climate environment monitoring system between the zhongshan station and the " dome - a " .
the ice hockey team , with a total membership of 13 people , is 54 years old and 26 years old , with an average age of over 40 .
seven of them had previously participated in the antarctic expedition and three of them had taken part in the scientific tour of high mountains and valleys in china .
zhang zhanhai said that this icecap scientific research project was basically carried out according to the plan , but it encountered many difficulties during this period .
the biggest test was that one of the eight snow sled parts was broken on the mechanical axis , rendering the entire team unable to move forward .
for this reason , the team members had no choice but to return 60 km back , and they continued to move forward after changing the new snow sled at the headquarters .
another difficulty is altitude reaction .
many members of the team reacted quite clearly and swiftly after climbing 3,800 meters above the mountain , and suffered a heart attack .
relying on the spirit of united struggle , the scientific expedition team overcame one difficulty after another on the road of advance .
