( world ) korea puts satellite digital multimedia broadcast on trial basis
xinhua news agency , seoul , january 10 ( reporter : zhang jinfang ) - south korea 's successful satellite digital multimedia broadcast on the 10 th marked the beginning of south korea 's satellite digital multimedia broadcast era .
the so - called satellite digital multimedia broadcasting refers to the satellite broadcasting in the form of multi - media broadcasting and television programs , which allows users to receive program signals through mobile terminals such as cell phones .
on the morning of the 10th , the ttadar media company , a subsidiary of the salk communications company , opened a total of nine channels in the satellite digital multimedia broadcast , including three television programs such as news , music , television dramas , and six music programs such as the latest popular songs , old songs , and jazz songs .
on the same day , salx telecommunications company introduced to the market the first batch of 250 mobile phones that can receive digital satellite multimedia broadcasting , and some users used these cell phones to receive the satellite digital multimedia broadcast programs .
it is reported that the rok government has listed the satellite digital multimedia broadcasting as a key scientific and technological development project and has given active support to enterprises in developing digital multimedia broadcasting technology and its products .
in april 2004 , the national assembly of the republic of korea passed the revised " broadcasting law " to allow satellite digital multimedia broadcasting .
at the end of 2003 , south korea 's salvos communications company and japanese enterprises jointly set up the ttms media company to prepare for the establishment of a satellite digital multimedia broadcasting station .
enterprises such as samsung electronics company and the h5n1 electronic company have successfully developed cell phones for receiving satellite digital multimedia broadcasting .
relevant departments in south korea have decided that satellite digital multimedia broadcasting will be put on trial for four months first , and formal broadcasting will begin in may this year .
( hong kong , macao and taiwan ) research institution forecasts : hong kong 's economy will grow by about 6% in 2005
xinhua news agency , hong kong , january 11 ( reporter su xiao ) the asia - pacific economic cooperation research center of the university of hong kong said on the 11 th that the global economic environment this year is still optimistic , and it is estimated that hong kong 's economy will grow by about 6 percent this year , and that it will grow by 4.4 percent annually in the first quarter .
wang yu , director of the hong kong university 's asia - pacific economic cooperation research center , said at a press conference on hong kong 's macro - economic forecast that although interest rates are expected to rise this year , hong kong 's major trading partners ' economic growth will slow , and the economies of the united states and the mainland of china will increase by 3.6% and 8.5% respectively , the global economic environment remains optimistic in 2005 .
he said that the center estimated that hong kong 's economy would maintain growth of about 6 percent in 2005 , while consumer prices would rise by 3 percent at the end of this year .
the adjustment of the labour market was still slow , and the unemployment rate would be slightly lowered to around 6.3% at the end of this year .
volatility in global oil prices remains a major uncertainties in our economy .
the deputy director of the institute , mr shao guangzhi , said that the economic growth momentum in the first quarter of this year would slow down , with gdp expected to grow 4.4% , reflecting a gradual decline in hong kong 's external demand , which was attributable to the slower economic growth of hong kong 's major trading partners .
according to the report , hong kong 's gross domestic product ( gdp ) recorded a strong growth of 8% in real terms in 2004 , with the average price level falling only slightly by 0.5% , while deflation also disappeared in the third quarter of last year .
zhou yeqing , chairman of the preparatory committee of the hong kong university 's " hong kong watch hong kong economic forecast " , said : hong kong 's strong economic growth in 2004 mainly reflects the solid foundation of the local economy , strong competitiveness in foreign trade markets , and the benefits of last year 's strong global economic growth and rapid growth of the mainland market economy . the end of the deflation problem will enable business people to enjoy more flow of cash .
